Submitting for 1st Level Approval 15
********************************************************************

Submit for 1st Level Approval
********************************************************************

1st Approval is all about you turning your project into something very interesting.  You will only be uploading high level details for this step.  Once an approver has looked it over, they may provide feedback/decline or approve your project so you can move on to the next step which is uploading the project details.


  • When you login to app.colaberry.com look to your panel to the left and click on Colaberry Network / Project Requests



  • Click on the Add Project button



This is the screen you will see next.





Project Title:  Here you will create a SHORT 4-10 word title.  Include the following...

What are you doing?

Which Industry Data?

Which Tools are you using?

Examples: 



Project Summary:  This summary is very important.  This is what will intrigue the user to click on your project.  Introduce a question or a crafty statement 1st to get them interested.  Here are some examples...




It is very important that the 1st sentence is crafty because that is the only thing that will be shown initially.  The user will have to click the more button to see the rest of the summary.

note: In some cases, your Problem statement will be a good fit here.  In other cases, it won't work.  You be the judge and if your Problem Statement fulfills the instructions above, then go ahead and use it as your summary.


Above is how a Project will look to the users.


Technology:  Which tools did you use to complete this project?  List them out.


Picture/Screenshot: Screenshot or find a picture of something that visually explains your project.  This picture will have the biggest impact on whether a user clicks on your project.  Currently the number 1 clicked on project is the following project created by Ali.  I (Ali) spent some good time using all the icons from the tools I used along with the websites my data was coming from along with a screenshot of a portion of my final Dashboard.  This could be a good format or you can go with an attractive picture that describes your project.


Project Checklist: You will need to make sure you upload the filled out checklist (Word Doc/zip) as part of this project request.  Projects will be rejected for leaving any of the above sections incomplete.

Make sure you fill out the ENTIRE checklist to ensure approval to the next step.  Good Luck!!!
